Zero is the symmetry point of a system.

Examples:

Mathematics
additive identity

Physics
equilibrium

Economics
break-even

Control systems
error = 0

Game theory
zero-sum boundary

Information theory
decision threshold

So zero marks the place where systems change behavior.

